<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments from the presidential
campaign trail:
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   
   GEORGE BUSH, speaking at the commencement Sunday of Central
State University, a predominantly black school in Wilberforce,
Ohio: ``I support strongly increased minority development efforts
by the federal government. We must bring black Americans and other
minorities into the free enterprise system.''
   
   JESSE JACKSON, asked Sunday whether Michael Dukakis is obligated
to offer him the vice presidential spot on the Democratic ticket:
``I do not want to push Mike Dukakis to that point.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, asked in a British television interview about
his supposed lack of charisma: ``I must be doing something right if
I've been able to come through this 15 months successfully. I'm not
a razzle-dazzle performer on the stage. I think I give a reasonably
decent speech, but my strength is in working with people, in
bringing people together, in my love of public service, in the
importance that I place on building coalitions.''
   
   GARREY CARRUTHERS, Republican governor of New Mexico, advising
George Bush on a potential running mate: ``I think we need an
exciting vice presidential candidate. We need someone, certainly,
who is a good communicator, like Ronald Reagan.''
   
   REP. PATRICIA SCHROEDER, D-Colo., in a speech this weekend in
which she criticized the lack of attention to family issues in the
presidential race: `We have so stylized the campaigns anymore
(that) we're going to have to outlaw decaffeinated coffee (until
after the election) or we'll all fall asleep.''
