<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF-Morgenthau-Drugs     06-13 0117</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF-Morgenthau-Drugs,0121</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Manhattan D.A. Announces Plan to Evict Drug Dealers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Manhattan District Attorney Robert Morgenthau
says he plans to start eviction proceedings against suspected drug
dealers or users whose apartments contain drugs found during legal
searches by police.
   Civil libertarians expressed dismay at the plan but said they
would review the statute on which Morgenthau was basing the policy.
   Morgenthau's program would cover tenants in both privately owned
and city-owned buildings.
   Gerald McKelvey, a spokesman for the district attorney, said the
law under which Morgenthau plans to seek the evictions states that
rental apartments cannot be used for illegal purposes.
   The action was outlined Sunday by Morgenthau on the WCBS-TV
program ``Newsmakers.''
</TEXT>
