<HEAD>Newspaper Prints Wrong Number for Nudist Colony; Woman Peeved</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Dikea is cq in lede.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>ST. CLAIR SHORES, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It's not that Dikea Edwards
necessarily dislikes nudists. She just doesn't like getting all
those bothersome telephone calls.
   The calls began after Metro Times, a weekly newspaper in the
Detroit area, published a summer activities guide last month that
listed Edwards' number as that of the Detroit Sun Club.
   Since then, she's received about 300 telephone calls asking
about the group.
   ``This has really annoyed me, I'll tell you,'' the 27-year-old
woman said.
   Metro Times Managing Editor Toni Swanger said the number was
correct in last year's guide, but no one checked it out for this
year's edition. The newspaper ran a correction, but that didn't
stop the calls.
   A directory assistance operator said today there is no listing
under the Detroit area code for the Detroit Sun Club.
