<HEAD>Three Angels Injured, One Critically, In Scuffle With Crack
Dealers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Guardian Angels founder Curtis Sliwa says the
group will not stop its effort to rid a section near Times Square
of drug dealers, even though one anti-crime patroller was
critically injured in a confrontation.
   ``We will continue to bang away, inch by inch, apartment
building by apartment building,'' Sliwa said Sunday. ``We will take
back the neighborhood.''
   Six Guardian Angels were injured and four people were arrested
in connection with the incident Saturday night.
   The Guardian Angels, a volunteer group, have been patrolling the
section at the request of restaurant owners in the theater district
who have complained that crack dealers are driving away their
customers.
   ``They're everywhere, like cockroaches,'' Sliwa said of the
dealers.
   Illya Lichtenberg, 16, of Verona, N.J., was in critical
condition today after he was hit in the head with a bottle and
stabbed in the chest during the confrontation between about 15
Guardian Angels and 15 other people on the street, according to
police and hospital spokesmen.
