<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Vietnam-Fire,0125</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Fire At Hospital in Vietnam Kills Two</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire at a hospital complex in Vietnam
killed two people and destroyed 50 houses, a report said Monday.
   The fire occurred at the Vietnam-Poland Friendship Hospital in
Vinh City, the capital of Nghe Tinh province 165 miles south of
Hanoi, according to a written text of a report by Radio Hanoi.
   The text was obtained from a Western embassy in Bangkok.
   ``The tools and property of 357 families, comprising 766 people,
at the complex, were burned to ashes,'' in the fire on Wednesday,
the report said. ``Losses in the fire were estimated 170 million
dong ($462,000).''
   The cause of the fire was under investigation, the report said.
</TEXT>
