<HEAD>Storm, Flash Floods Kill 16 In Turkey</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANKARA, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A violent thunderstorm and flash floods
killed 16 people in Turkey, a governor said Monday.
   Ankara's slums were hardest hit Sunday evening.
   About 100 houses were damaged, and the majority of the victims
died when their homes were flooded, Ankara Gov. Saffet Arikan Beduk
said on state radio.
   Six of the people who died were electrocuted, Beduk said. They
included a 13-year-old boy who was struck by lightning, the
Hurriyet News Agency reported.
