<HEAD>People In The News</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY44</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: First two items are for Release 6:30 p.m. EDT</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Big, tough Sylvester Stallone says he was once a
skinny runt, ``a major ectomorph'' who other kids called ``Sylvia.''
   Stallone recalled growing up poor in New York's rough Hell's
Kitchen section, in an interview published in the July Ladies' Home
Journal. He said he was taunted by other children for his
appearance and speech problems.
   ``I was born by a forceps delivery, and the forceps severed a
nerve on the left side of my face,'' he explained.
   As he got older, Stallone said, he got wilder. ``I used to beat
up on cars, beat up on authority. Anything to shock. I still
sometimes do things just for shock value. I suppose the need for
attention, that insecure little boy, is still rattling around
inside.''
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Kathleen Turner's latest role _ the real
life one of a new mother _ seems to be one that will influence her
future role choices.
   ``The thought of my kid coming home from school one day and
saying, `So-and-so saw you naked''' is a concern for her, Turner
said in an interview in the Ladies' Home Journal.
   Turner who's first child, Rachel Ann, is nine months old, has
starred in such sexy films as ``Body Heat.''
</TEXT>
<NOTE>Eds: For Release at 6 p.m. EDT</NOTE>
<DATELINE>RADNOR, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The vote is in for the 1988 all-star nightly
news team with Peter Jennings, described as ``the least
aggravating'' and Tom Brokaw, ``the most natural without seeming
silly or confused,'' tying as best anchors in a tight race.
   The team was elected by an informal panel of judges assembled by
TV Guide, which notes in its June 18 issue, ``that if sports has
all-star teams, maybe TV news should have one, too.''
   ABC's White House correpsondent Sam Donaldson was also among
those honored ``even though ... he often oversteps journalistic
bounds,'' said one judge, critic David Shaw.
