<HEAD>Lily Tomlin: No Animosity Toward Co-Star Bette Midler</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lily Tomlin disputes rumors she and ``Big
Business'' co-star Bette Midler fought during filming, saying
emphatically that they are good friends and that the warmth comes
across on the screen.
   In the film, which opened last weekend, Ms. Tomlin and Miss
Midler each play a pair of identical twins who are mixed up at
birth and raised as fraternal twins. One set winds up in a
hillbilly hollow; the second set lives luxuriously in New York.
   ``I'm very fond of Bette and I felt that we were cute
together,'' Ms. Tomlin said. ``I thought if we could be to the
ultimate what we both are, it could be super.''
   Ms. Tomlin, who has played a disgruntled secretary in ``9 to
5,'' a happy housewife who became ``The Incredible Shrinking
Woman'' and a body snatcher in ``All of Me,'' is working on an
animated special for CBS, based on the character Edith Ann, a
mischievous 5-year-old.
   Asked if she ever has the urge to play a more mainstream role,
she said: ``Not really. Shrinking women, body snatchers, these are
the things movies are made of.''
