Martin and Wall Street Journal national security correspondent John
Walcott said North proposed asking Waite to go to Tripoli to meet
with Gadhafi.
   Waite would ask Gadhafi's help in freeing the American hostages
in Lebanon and then depart, leaving the Libyan leader to spend the
night at his compound _ where he could be the target of an
