<HEAD>Practical Joker Driving Man Bananas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GREENEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Alvin Wallace is going bananas. Or,
rather, bananas are going to Alvin Wallace.
   A couple of banana trees were stolen from his yard in
Greeneville in April.
   Wallace didn't bother to complain to police but he did tell
friends.
   Since May 31, a practical joker has sent him several dozen
bananas. One bunch was accompanied by vanilla ice cream; another
was black and rotten.
   Wallace said the bananas have been delivered to his office at
G&W Hauling and Rigging through a courier service sworn to secrecy.
   He thinks he's narrowed down the culprit to a fishing buddy; an
empty box containing only the message ``blue gill'' was delivered
Monday.
   He has reciprocated with a couple of shipments of his own _
banana pudding and banana bread.
   ``Now it's my turn,'' he said.
