<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Sullivan,0141</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Editorial Cartoonist for Worcester Telegram Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WORCESTER, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert T. Sullivan, an editorial
cartoonist for the Worcester Telegram for 17 years, has died
following a short illness. He was 64.
   Sullivan, whose lifelong ambition was cartooning, began his
career as a manufacturer's representative in power transmissions
but worked as a free-lance cartoonist until he joined the Telegram
in 1971.
   A World War II veteran who received the Air Medal for his
missions as a top turret gunner over France, Sullivan contributed
drawings to the military newspaper Stars and Stripes.
   He received numerous awards for his editorial cartoons, which
also have been displayed in several area galleries.
   Dick Locher, editorial cartoonist for the Chicago Tribune,
called Sullivan ``a tremendous artist and excellent cartoonist.''
   Sullivan leaves three brothers. Funeral services are scheduled
Wednesday.
