<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Japanese     06-13 0221</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Japanese,0231</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>NEC Earnings Rise 69 Percent In Fiscal Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NEC Corp., the Japanese electronics giant, said
its profit rose 68.7 percent in its latest fiscal year from the
depressed level of a year earlier, partly because of a recovery in
its world-leading sales of semiconductors. Sales climbed 10.8
percent.
   The company predicted further gains in its current fiscal year,
which ends March 31, 1989, estimating gains of about 90 percent in
profit and 7 percent in sales.
   NEC said its profit rose to 25.4 billion yen, or about $205
million, from 10.3 billion yen in the previous year. Revenue rose
to 2.71 trillion yen, or $21.9 billion, from 2.45 trillion yen a
year earlier.
   NEC announced its profits on Friday in Tokyo, but the report was
not circulated in the United States until Monday.
   In addition to a recovered market for semiconductors, NEC cited
``steady progress'' in such fields as communications equipment,
computers, industrial electronic systems and home electronics.
   Domestic sales rose 12.2 percent and overseas sales rose 7.2
percent. Equity in earnings of affiliated companies _ mainly
subsidiaries in the United States and other countries _ jumped 146
percent, partly on the strength of a stronger yen.
   The results in yen were translated into dollars at a rate of 124
yen to the dollar.
</TEXT>
