<2ND_LINE>BC-Weekly Steel,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steel Output Fell 1.3 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production fell to 1.944 million tons in
the week ended June 11, a decrease of 1.3 percent from the previous
week's 1.969 million tons, the American Iron and Steel Institute
reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 90.7 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 91.9 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
45.482 million net tons, a rise of 23.6 percent from the 36.785
million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 91.0 percent of capacity,
compared with 73.8 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended June 11: Northeast
Coast, 277,000; Pittsburgh, 203,000; Youngstown, 118,000; Lake
Erie, 171,000; Detroit, 159,000; Chicago, 510,000; Midwest,
189,000; Southern, 218,000; and Western, 99,000.
